MyBroadbandâ€™s 2017 Salary Survey has revealed that growth potential and professional development are the most important factors in contributing to the happiness of IT professionals in South Africa. The survey was completed by 3,062 South Africans who work in the IT sector, and included executives and professionals from large tech companies. IT professionals who completed the survey indicated that they were generally happy at work, with an average happiness score of 6.7 out of 10. The survey results showed that programmers and developers are generally very happy in their jobs, while tech support, networking professionals, and designers are the unhappiest. Other important factors for happiness were salary, a good work-life balance, and interesting work. Company benefits, recognition for work, and job security were ranked as the least-important factors which determined happiness. 